main event: A bright yellowish-white object was observed moving at high speed for about 20 seconds, 100-135 miles southeast of the Azores.
interesting points: The object was reported to have a very bright appearance that shined through overcast conditions., The sighting occurred while a US Coast Guard cutter was in position (35N/22S)., The object moved from west to east, disappearing out of sight in approximately 10 seconds., The conclusions included multiple possible explanations such as a meteor, balloons, or aircraft., No photographs of the sighting are included in the report.
location: 100-135 MI SE of Azores, Azores, Portugal
witness description: US Coast Guard personnel aboard the cutter 'Eagle'
